    <h1>OverEasy&#x2019;s Hol&#xAD;i&#xAD;day Spe&#xAD;cials For Kids Hard Rock Cafe Singapore&#x2019;s $15 Three-Course Set Lunch</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200911/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-11"><time>2020-09-11</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>At OverEasy at One Fuller­ton, chil­dren un­der the age of 12 can dine in for free to­day. With every adult main course, the lit­tle ones can en­joy their own fun-sized clas­sics, such as Momma’s Chicken & Waf­fles with but­ter­milk fried chicken on house­made waf­fles with warm maple but­ter, Grilled Three Cheese Sand­wich with Tomato Soup, Good Ol’ Fash­ioned Mac & Cheese or The OverEasy Cheese­burger.</p>
    <p>WHERE: 01-06 One Fuller­ton, 1 Fuller­ton Road MRT: Raf­fles Place WHEN: To­day, noon - 3pm</p>
    <p>PRICE: Sig­na­ture Steak & Egg: $44 INFO: overeasy.com.sg/reser­va­tions</p>
    <p>The menu com­prises a soup of the day, a main (op­tions in­clude clas­sics such as cheese­burger and baby back ribs), a sin­gle scoop of Haa­gen-Dazs ice cream and a bev­er­age (Coke, Sprite or iced lemon tea). Avail­able for dine-in and take­away. The pro­mo­tion is not avail­able on pub­lic hol­i­days.</p>
    <p>WHERE: 02-01 HPL House, 50 Cus­ca­den Road MRT: Or­chard WHEN: Week­days, 11.30am - 3pm INFO: face­book.com/ hardrock­cafesin­ga­pore</p>


